occupation grunt.definition: An audible grunt, cough, or clearing of the throat issued by an [individual] while using a stall in a public men's restroom, especially when they hear [someone else] entering. This is done to advise the incoming patron that the stall is occupied, helping them avoid any awkward attempts to [open the door] or worse, peer through the crack in the door. A grunt is best because this bypasses any dialogue or conversation- both of which are widely regarded as taboo in a public men's room.
